caption: Every single time we come here they never have Mac and cheese. They just don't want to do their job
This place is pretty mid. I wouldn’t go here again.  The meatball sub is pretty lame and soggy and the cookies are literally rocks. Go to Subway for better bang for your buck.

Came in around 11am today with 3 customers in line and 3 employees. All of the employees looked like they hated being there, didn't acknowledge/greet any customers. It took almost 15 mins to get through the line because the cashier only cared about the online orders. The customer in front of me finally got his food and was ready to pay but the cashier decided to make an online order instead of just letting the man who is on his lunch break pay and be on his way after waiting so long. To top it off, I ordered the medditeranean sandwhich which clearly states that it comes with chicken, to see that after the man passed it through the toaster, there was no chicken on it. I decided not to say anything as I knew it would take forever to redo the sandwhich at this point. There is a lack of communication and care at this location and it shows big time. I understand if you're busy, but simple communication with customers and acknowledging them goes a long way.
Always top notch food! Easy to order ahead and pick up in person. Delicious! A Chicago classic! Did you know Potbelly actually started in Chicago?

Went in this potbelly’s on a Sunday, there’s a few workers inside no one says anything when I walk in, they were all quit and not very inviting, actually pretty depressing in there. I get 5 sandwiches which they didn’t label so has to go through them all at home, they gave my a turkey BLT without the turkey! I asked for a large smoothie and they gave me the regular size when I said I asked for a large they told me that was the large... so I had to explain I’ve always gotten it in the 16 oz cup at other stores. I just said forget it and left. I also ordered online from this store a few weeks ago and they gave me the wrong sandwich all together. It seemed like everyone was young and didn’t get trained well.

My wife ordered 4 sandwiches for delivery and only got 3. She called the store and told them that she only gotten 3 and they made it seem like she was lying. No apology was given manager couldn't even be bothered to take her call. The manager told the middle person that we won't be sending out for a delivery for only 1 sandwich. My wife ended up having to pick up the missing sandwich. So she paid for delivery and she still needed to go and pick up food. Very disappointed on the service and making her feel like she was lying.
A preferred evening place. The bill was fair.
Love the sandwiches..peppers are a must to kill all other pains..lol

If you want something delivered, expect sloppy incorrect orders, and if you get every item you ordered, you are lucky.  It's clear there is a huge disconnect with the staff at this location.  Maybe poor pay or poor training but you can tell no one takes pride in the work they do.  Other reviewers are dead on, place is ALWAYS dirty.  Even if when it's empty (and often is prior to Covid)

Firstly, I understand we are in the middle of a pandemic. Secondly, I still would appreciate receiving what I ordered, or at least be reimbursed for the items I didn't receive.  They go through a 3rd party delivery service, so they couldn't bring my items....fine.  When I called they said they hadn't processed the payment and would take off what I didn't get.  At that point my husband's card was already charged.....mmmmm....okay.  I called back and they told me 5-7 business he would be reimbursed.  He has yet to be reimbursed and it has been over 7 days I will NEVER go there again.

For some reason, EVERY TIME I order delivery from here they add giardiniera to my sandwich. Every time. There’s no reason for this since I literally only ask for lettuce mayo and meat, and it’s not the delivery service since I do not add giardiniera to the sandwich through the app. Guys please, lay off the giardiniera!!!!!!!!

For service on 3/1/2020 at 12:30 PM.  Very unfriendly and disengaged service, dirty tables (which patrons were cleaning for themselves), and dry chicken on grilled chicken sandwich).  Cookies were excellent, though!

This location is horrible. Any time we order for delivery, their site finds some way to screw it up. Sometimes it gets flagged for pickup, other times it gets delivered to the wrong address. They will accept zero accountability for their shortcomings and place the blame on the customer. Customer service is non-existent. My interactions with this location has made me ponder ever to frequent the chain at all.

I posted a review about 5 months ago. I still love the food here. However, the workers here are rude now and the place is filthy, all the time, even at times when there is seemingly no customers (I came in and I was the only one in the whole store and it was still filthy). I don't understand. Hope this place can get back to how it was. Disappointed.

The guys working here are very nice. Great customer service. They respect the kids too which I thought was impressive.  It’s nice to know that everyone’s children can come to the neighborhood potbelly and be treated respectfully. Kudos to you guys!  I don’t know the guys names but it’s 3:30 pm on Tuesday, January 14th, 2020.
The food is always delicious, fresh, and great customer service.

I went to lunch during my lunch period at potbelly today with my friends who had brought pizza from another place but a good majority of us had bought food from potbelly. One of the workers then took it upon herself to cause a huge scene. She singled my table out and started yelling at us telling us to get the hell out and that she would call the cops. No one has said anything against outside food before and she did not tell us prior that it was not allowed. If she had told us nicely or mentioned it before we would have been fine with it. Afterwords we all just left calmly. This behavior was completely unprofessional and I will most definetly not be coming back here again.

Potbelly’s food is great everywhere but this one probably has the nicest workers I’ve seen. The tall black lady with long hair is especially great, think she’s been working there for a while

Avid Potbelly fan.  I used to know the manager of this particular one, since I used to be an employee.  I go in for my regular.  Light skinned latino guy at DRESS is making sandwiches fine, when my sandwich comes up - mid process, he pulls out a long hair.  He pulls the hair off my sandwich, and kind of out of his glove - it was connected to his glove.  Then proceeds to finish the sandwich...  But he stops, and replaces the sandwhich.  Cool. Maybe he just had to have the thought process - i stayed silent.  He continues making the sandwiches with the contaminated gloves - my first thought would be to change gloves (Where did the hair come from?). He doesn't, makes a few more sandwhiches - mine is now on the fly.  expedited. when mine comes out, i asked him to change his gloves.  I am a little paranoid.  Not the worst thing?  I made sure to say thank you - which he ignored. Ok whatever.  Heres where im really surprised: He gets a potent attitude and slops together a sandwich with all the toppings in the middle? ...  I am usually pretty calm.  Not too picky. And I love potbelly.  And i have worked there. This dude doesn't know customer service, because I was just aggress-ed at for requesting a clean sandwich.  Void of hair. That's not extreme, and is not asking for too much effort. I didn't make a scene. I just got my money back.  Dude needs to be trained  He is the "unperfect hinge," at this location

Yesterday I went to this potbelly and I needed to use the restroom really bad. In the restroom someone was banging on the door and wouldn’t stop banging on it so after I was done with my business I opened the door and a potbelly worker was yelling at me saying I can’t have more than one person in the bathroom and that she saw me in the camera. She proceeded to yell at me when literally nobody else came out except me from that bathroom and I wanted an explanation as to why she was being so rude to a CUSTOMER but she just went back to the employee only area.

Tasty sandwiches and fresh ingredients. They've been nothing but kind to me, even started remembering my order. If you are a quiet vegan like me, they won't bat an eyelash if you ask for a Mediterranean, no meat, no cheese, and ask them for every veggie known to man. I spend at least five hours here a week and with good reason. Fast, tasty, pleasent, even when there is 10 people in line.
Great Service! My sandwich was on point!!!
Really good sandwich, service was fast for the most part. Good local location.
I love Potbelly.  Their sandwiches are great. They were pretty busy today but we were served quickly with little delay.

Great service. Very friendly and fast!

I will never rate Potbelly's less than four stars. Four only if my shake is too thin or they screw up my mustard. But all around my favorite sandwich place with great food, great service, great people, and even better root beer.
Love this place

My husband and I have fallen in love with the new Potbelly Cuban sandwich. So much so that we had these twice in one week. Once my husband picked up the sandwiches, and the next time we took advantage of their delivery service. The only reason I give four out of five stars is because sometimes there is live music playing at any/all Potbelly's, and when we go to a casual spot to eat, we often sit and read. I wish I knew when the restaurant had live music, and when it didn't.
One of the best Potbelly's I've been to. Always consistent with their sandwiches and delicious.
I ate a sandwich that was 100% what I  expected.
nice size restaurant. inexpensive good sandwiches good location

Potbelly's has always been a really good sandwich shop. The staff here is really nice. Recommends good things to try and they actually enjoy being at work. Lovely people. My new favorite lunch spot from work.

Good food

The area behind the counter was an absolute disaster. Not clean. The excuse given was that it was the lunch rush. I've seen this place cleaner during rush hours with less staff. There was enough staff today to do a quick 20min sprucing up.  Not a good image for a large brand. I added one additional star because despite their lack of attention to detail for the clean area, they still delivered on the customer service aspect. To the manager here, clean appearance gives confidence to the customer in your product and it's also good customer service.
Great fast staff! Gets extremely busy. Bathrooms are dirty.
Always a great place to grab a quick sandwich. Staff is always nice and friendly. They have parking but its tight and the Starbucks drive thru gets in the way of getting into the parking lot.

Typical Potbelly's, but this one is usually less crowded than the one in Lincoln Square. Friendly staff, pretty good sandwiches. I'm glad they recently added the turkey club to the regular menu. The chocolate brownie cookie is irresistible.
I have gone to multiple Potbellys and by far this one has the nicest most efficient workers. Their food is delicious. The store is very clean. I really enjoyed my experience there.
Pretty good sandwich place. I'm pretty specific about my sandwiches, and I did get something yummy! The "big" is not that big, but nothing is overpriced so it's okay.
